.TH "PERFORMANCERESOURCETIMING.FINALRESPONSEHEADERSSTART" "3JS" "February 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
PerformanceResourceTiming.finalResponseHeadersStart \-
PerformanceResourceTiming: finalResponseHeadersStart property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]finalResponseHeadersStart\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property
returns a \f[CR]timestamp\f[R] immediately after the browser receives
the first byte of the final document response (for example, 200 OK) from
the server.
.PP
This differs from \f[B]\f[CB]requestStart\f[B]\f[R] (which may also be
represented as \f[B]\f[CB]firstInterimResponseStart\f[B]\f[R]), as this
starts from the first bytes of any response including interim responses
(for example, 103 Early Hints) with the final response coming
potentially much later.
.PP
When there are no interim responses, \f[CR]requestStart\f[R] is the same
as \f[CR]finalResponseHeadersStart\f[R] and
\f[CR]firstInterimResponseStart\f[R] is 0.
.PP
There is no \f[I]end\f[R] property for
\f[CR]finalResponseHeadersStart\f[R].
.SH VALUE
The \f[CR]finalResponseHeadersStart\f[R] property can have the following
values:
.IP \(bu 2
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] immediately after the browser receives
the first bytes of the final response from the server.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]0\f[R] if the resource is a cross\-origin request and no
\f[CR]Timing\-Allow\-Origin\f[R] HTTP response header is used.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Measuring request time
The \f[CR]finalResponseHeadersStart\f[R] and \f[CR]requestStart\f[R]
properties can be used to measure how long it takes for the browser to
start receive the final response after the sending the request.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] request = entry.finalResponseHeadersStart \- entry.requestStart;
.EE
.PP
The following example uses a \f[CR]PerformanceObserver\f[R] to notify of
new \f[CR]resource\f[R] performance entries as they are recorded in the
browser\(cqs performance timeline.
The \f[CR]buffered\f[R] option is used for accessing entries from before
the observer creation.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] observer = \f[B]new\f[R] PerformanceObserver((list) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  list.getEntries().forEach((entry) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    \f[B]const\f[R] request = entry.finalResponseHeadersStart \- entry.requestStart;
    \f[B]if\f[R] (request > 0) {
      console.log(\(ga${entry.name}: final response time: ${request}ms\(ga);
    }
  });
});

observer.observe({ type: \(dqresource\(dq, buffered: \f[B]true\f[R] });
.EE
.PP
The following example uses \f[CR]Performance.getEntriesByType()\f[R],
which only shows \f[CR]resource\f[R] performance entries present in the
browser\(cqs performance timeline at the time you call the method.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] resources = performance.getEntriesByType(\(dqresource\(dq);
resources.forEach((entry) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] request = entry.finalResponseHeadersStart \- entry.requestStart;
  \f[B]if\f[R] (request > 0) {
    console.log(\(ga${entry.name}: final response time: ${request}ms\(ga);
  }
});
.EE
.PP
The following example shows how to measure the time between the first
and final response headers.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] observer = \f[B]new\f[R] PerformanceObserver((list) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  list.getEntries().forEach((entry) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    \f[B]const\f[R] diff = entry.finalResponseHeadersStart \- entry.responseStart;
    \f[B]if\f[R] ((entry.finalResponseHeadersStart > 0) & (diff > 0)) {
      console.log(
        \(ga${entry.name}: time between first and final response start: ${diff}ms\(ga,
      );
    }
  });
});

observer.observe({ type: \(dqresource\(dq, buffered: \f[B]true\f[R] });
.EE
.SS Cross\-origin timing information
If the value of the \f[CR]finalResponseHeadersStart\f[R] property is
\f[CR]0\f[R], the resource might be a cross\-origin request.
To allow seeing cross\-origin timing information, the
\f[CR]Timing\-Allow\-Origin\f[R] HTTP response header needs to be set.
.PP
For example, to allow \f[CR]https://developer.mozilla.org\f[R] to see
timing resources, the cross\-origin resource should send:
.IP
.EX
Timing\-Allow\-Origin: https://developer.mozilla.org
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Timing\-Allow\-Origin\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]firstInterimResponseStart\f[R]
